+AI:+A+Review+of+Machine+Learning+Interpretability+Methods&author=Linardatos,+P.&author=Papastefanopoulos,+V.&author=Kotsiantis,+S.&publication_year=2020&journal=Entropy&volume=23&pages=18&doi=10.3390/e23010018" class='google-scholar' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Google Scholar</a>] [<a href="https://doi.org/10.3390/e23010018" class='cross-ref' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>CrossRef</a>]</li><li id='B35-electronics-13-04570' class='html-xx' data-content='35.'>Guidotti, R.; Monreale, A.; Ruggieri, S.; Turini, F.; Pedreschi, D.; Giannotti, F. A Survey Of Methods For Explaining Black Box Models. <span class='html-italic'>ACM Comput. Surv.</span> <b>2018</b>, <span class='html-italic'>51</span>, 1–42. [<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=A+Survey+Of+Methods+For+Explaining+Black+Box+Models&author=Guidotti,+R.&author=Monreale,+A.&author=Ruggieri,+S.&author=Turini,+F.&author=Pedreschi,+D.&author=Giannotti,+F.&publication_year=2018&journal=ACM+Comput.+Surv.&volume=51&pages=1%E2%80%9342&doi=10.1145/3236009" class='google-scholar' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Google Scholar</a>] [<a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3236009" class='cross-ref' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>CrossRef</a>]</li><li id='B36-electronics-13-04570' class='html-xx' data-content='36.'>Nguyen, Q.P.; Lim, K.W.; Divakaran, D.M.; Low, K.H.; Chan, M.C. GEE: A Gradient-based Explainable Variational Autoencoder for Network Anomaly Detection. In Proceedings of the 2019 IEEE Conference on Communications and Network Security (CNS), Washington, DC, USA, 10–12 June 2019. [<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=GEE:+A+Gradient-based+Explainable+Variational+Autoencoder+for+Network+Anomaly+Detection&conference=Proceedings+of+the+2019+IEEE+Conference+on+Communications+and+Network+Security+(CNS)&author=Nguyen,+Q.P.&author=Lim,+K.W.&author=Divakaran,+D.M.&author=Low,+K.H.&author=Chan,+M.C.&publication_year=2019" class='google-scholar' ta